AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp; The Council of Ministers, in the light of an information carried out by the Minister of the Interior, Matteo Piantedosi, has decided to give mandate to the Attorney General for the purpose of the appeal in Cassation warns the decision of the Court of Appeal of Rome of 24 January 2024, concerning the methods of issue and the characteristics of the electronic identity card (CIE), governed by the interministerial decree of 23 December 2015 and subsequent modifications, which provides for minors
&nbsp;
The Court of Appeal ruling on the use of a couple of omogenital parents against the Salvini decree, had maintained the parental wording 1 and parent 2.&nbsp; Salvini rejected it as "a wrong decision" and today the Council of Ministers decided to bring the case to the Palazzaccio.&nbsp;

