AGI -&nbsp; Despite the choice to put the candidacy in Bari in the hands of the parties, the Movement 5 Stars keeps the bar straight on Michele Laforgia, the name chosen together with Sinistra Italiana. It is the line indicated by the regional levels of the party of Giuseppe Conte a few minutes from the river conference in which Laforgia announced: "The decision of my candidacy to the mayor of Bari is put to the hands of the parties that have me candidate and the political forces that are in the field for the administrative elections of 2024". Words to which the candidate of Pd and Europa Verde, Vito Leccese answers: "I hope it's not a new waste of time."
&nbsp;
To leave Leccese puzzled is the reference to the decision given to the parties. The deadline for submitting lists is 28 April. Just three weeks, therefore, to develop a program and indicate a coalition candidate. And, on the other hand, to scan sources of Pd and M5s, the move of Laforgia does not compact the forces in the field. The local levels of the Five Stars, in fact, let us know to be determined to keep the bar straight on the chosen candidate with Italian Left.
&nbsp;
"We appreciate the words and the great commitment of Michele Laforgia, candidate mayor to the administrations of Bari. Its readiness to stay in the field shows the seriousness and coherence of those who care about the future of the city. We firmly confirm our support for his candidacy," explains Leonardo Donno, MP and coordinator M5s in Puglia. The secretary of SI, Nicola Fratoianni, had invited Laforgia and Leccese to find an agreement between them, allowing it not to be indisputable to accept a possible step back of its candidate.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
And after the candidate's conference, Fratoianni says: "We thank Michele Laforgia for doing a further step this evening in the interest of the city of Bari. His choice to deliver in the hands of the Convention we are part of and of the other political forces that have supported him to find a solution capable of determining a step forward is, for us, a positive fact. From tomorrow, as we have done all these days, we will continue to work so that we can identify a unitary and shared solution," concludes Fratoianni. Sources of the Democratic Party at work on the Bari dossier emphasize that the choice of Laforgia opens a space that needs to be filled. Therefore, it is underlined, the interlocution goes on among all parties in the field. Laforgia, on the other hand, accompanied his readiness to question the candidacy by words that make leak his ill mood for the situation that came to be created after the opening of the investigation on the alleged votes of exchange in the Barese who also involved a councillor of the Emilian junta.
&nbsp;
"I'm asked to do something that I have no intention of doing," said the criminal lawyer: "Here, one step back and at the same time choose, seek or propose another candidate or another candidate. Since all this reasoning presupposes that I have become for someone or for someone, a lightning strike, we remove this lightning: the responsibility is yours, take it in front of the city today and for everything that will happen in the coming months". In the face of all this, the Movement renews the invitation because&nbsp;Pd and Green Europe converge on Laforgia: "Even today, the Democratic Party did not provide evidence of the candidacy of Laforgia, considered authoritative and esteemed by all. We therefore ask you to make a choice for the good of the Bari community and to avoid delivering the city to the worst right. We hope that there will be convergence on the civic name of Laforgia."

