AGI - In Sardinia the election day is planned, with the municipalities rushed to the European elections of 8-9 June next. The decision will already be taken next Thursday, in two days, when the president of the Region, Alessandra Todde, will convene the first meeting of his Junta that swore today in the Regional Council Hall. "The intention is to realize European and administrative, not only to save public money but also because the temporal window would not have justified a different choice. We'll catch you on a unique day." "It is important," the president added, "to immediately define a working method and priorities with the members of the Junta".
&nbsp;
"We have to allow the offices to train and give the councillors the opportunity to have a team of full staff," said Todde. "An orderly delivery with your predecessors is planned. We must address the priorities, starting with the health issue we brought last week to the State-Regions Conference, and that of the ban on territorial continuity in due course, on which I met the offices in the past weeks. I will discuss it as soon as possible with the Councillor for Transport"
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> The new Council
The sitting was chaired by the oldest, Lorenzo Cozzolino. President <a href="https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2024-03-20/regional-elections-alessandra-todde-proclamata-president-sardegna-25782554/">Alessandra Todde</a>, who read his communications and presented the new Junta. The four younger councillors present at the sitting have served as secretary. To read the names of the colleagues was the exponent of the M5S, re-elected, Alessandro Solinas. The new councillors who have not already done so as councillors: Maria Elena Motzo (General Affairs, Personnel), Francesco Spanedda (Local and Urbanist Organizations), Rosanna Laconi (Environment), Emanuele Cani (Industry), Ilaria Portas (Public Education, Cultural Heritage, Armando Bartolazzi (Sanity), Barbara Manca (Transport). Shortly before they had sworn as advisers Giuseppe Meloni del Pd (Programmation and Budget), Antonio More than Alleanza Verdi Sinistra (Public Works), Franco Cuccureddu of Orizzonte Comune (Turismo, Artigianato e Commercio), Desire' Manca del M5S (Lavoro) and Gianfranco Satta dei Progressisti (Agriculture). &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
&nbsp;
In the seventeenth legislature there are 25 outgoing and 35 re-elected members of the Regional Council. The women are 10: in addition to the president of the Junta, Todde, there are six representatives of the majority of the centerleft (Desirè Manca and Lara Serra del M5S, Maria Laura Orrù di Alleanza Verdi Sinistra, Camilla Soru and Carla Fundoni del Pd, Paola Casula di Sinistra Futura and three of the opposition of the center-right (Alice Aroni dell'Ud Franca, Cristina Usai and Cristina Usai).
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> The election of Comandini</h2>
Piero Comandini, secretary of the Sardinian Pd, is the new president of the Regional Council of Sardinia. The House elected this morning a secret vote in the settlement session, to the third vote with a simple majority, with 42 votes, those of the entire centre-left (36), plus a part of the minority. The rest of the opposition voted white card (16), apart from a preference for the centrist Antonello Peru. There was also a tab nothing. The votes for Comandini have distinguished themselves for different words: Mrs Comandini, Comandini G.P., Comandini Giampietro, Piero Comandini, Comandini Giampiero and the only surname. The reading of the outcome of the vote was received by a long applause in the Chamber and Comandini, visibly moved and excited, received hugs and handshakes from the nearby counter and then also by President Alessandra Todde.

&nbsp;
In the first vote, where a majority of 40 councillors were required, 33 abstained and the votes were 27, of which 21 white cards and nothing. In Comandini two preferences had gone, two at the exponent of Sardinia at the Centro Venti20 Antonello Peru. In the second, in which a qualified majority was always required but white cards were also counted, they voted 53 advisors out of 60; the abstained were 32, the voters 21; 14 white cards. Six votes went to Peru, one to the provisional president of the Assembly, Lorenzo Cozzolino. "My thanks go to all 60 regional councillors," Comandini said on his arm from the highest scranno in the House. "We must fly high, undress us from our political affiliations, without denying them. At this moment we must have in front of us only Sardinia and Sardinia". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

